INIT().notice: Initialization function for the module which is called when the module is         first installed or upgraded by the kernel. Can only be called by the kernel.

KEYCODE().notice: Defines the keycode for this module.

MODULE_PROXY_INSTANTIATION(address).notice: Instantiates this contract as a module via a proxy.

VERSION().notice: Specifies which version of a module is being implemented.

addRentalSafe(address).notice: Adds the addresss of a rental safe to storage so that protocol-deployed         rental safes can be distinguished from those deployed elsewhere.

addRentals(bytes32,(bytes32,uint256)[]).notice: Adds an order hash to storage. Once an order hash is added to storage,         the assets contained within are considered actively rented. Additionally,         rental asset IDs are added to storage which creates a blocklist on those         assets. When the blocklist is active, the protocol guard becomes active on         them and prevents transfer or approval of the assets by the owner of the         safe.

applyFine(address,uint256).notice: Apply a fine to a user.

assetEnabledForRent(address).notice: Determines whether the asset is enabled for renting in the protocol

assetRestrictedForPermit(address).notice: Determines whether the asset is restricted for gasless permit().

banUser(address,uint256).notice: Temporarily ban a user by setting an expiry timestamp.

blacklistUser(address).notice: Blacklist a user, preventing them from participating in the marketplace.

changeKernel(address).notice: Points the adapter to reference a new kernel address. This function can         only be called by the active kernel, and is used to perform migrations by         telling all policies and modules where the new kernel is located before         actually performing the migration.

clearFine(address).notice: Clear a user's fine, resetting the amount to zero.

contractToHook(address).notice: Fetches the hook address that is pointing at the the target.

extensionDisableAllowed(address).notice: Determines whether the extension can be disabled on the rental safe.

extensionEnableAllowed(address).notice: Determines whether the extension can be enabled on the rental safe.

freeze().notice: Freezes the contract which prevents upgrading the implementation contract.         There is no way to unfreeze once a contract has been frozen.

hookOnStart(address).notice: Determines whether the `onStart()` function is enabled for the hook.

hookOnStop(address).notice: Determines whether the `onStop()` function is enabled for the hook.

hookOnTransaction(address).notice: Determines whether the `onTransaction()` function is enabled for the hook.

isRentedOut(address,address,uint256).notice: Determines if an asset is actively being rented by a wallet.

isUserBanned(address).notice: Check if a user is currently banned.

issueWarning(address).notice: Record a warning for a user.

proxiableUUID().notice: Returns the ID of this `Proxiable` contract.

removeRentals(bytes32,(bytes32,uint256)[.notice: Removes an order hash from storage. Once an order hash is removed from         storage, it can no longer be stopped since the protocol will have no         record of the order. Addtionally, rental asset IDs are removed from         storage. Once these hashes are removed, they are no longer blocklisted         from being transferred out of the rental wallet by the owner.

removeRentalsBatch(bytes32[],(bytes32,ui.notice: Behaves the same as `removeRentals()`, except that orders are processed in          a loop.

setGuardEmergencyUpgrade(address).notice: Sets the guard emergency upgrade address.

setMaxConsiderationItems(uint256).notice: Sets the maximum consideration items for a single order.

setMaxOfferItems(uint256).notice: Sets the maximum offer items for a single order.

toggleWhitelistAsset(address,uint8).notice: Toggles whether a token can be rented.

toggleWhitelistAssetBatch(address[],uint.notice: Toggles whether a batch of tokens can be rented.

toggleWhitelistDelegate(address,bool).notice: Toggles whether an address can be delegate called.

toggleWhitelistExtension(address,uint8).notice: Updates an extension with a bitmap that indicates whether the extension         can be enabled or disabled by the rental safe. A valid bitmap is any         decimal value that is less than or equal to 3 (0x11).

toggleWhitelistPayment(address,bool).notice: Toggles whether a token can be used as a payment.

toggleWhitelistPaymentBatch(address[],bo.notice: Toggles whether a batch of tokens can be used as payment.

unblacklistUser(address).notice: Remove a user from the blacklist, allowing them to participate again.

updateHookPath(address,address).notice: Connects a hook to a destination address. Once an active path is made,         any transactions originating from a rental safe to the target address         will use a hook as middleware. The hook chosen is determined by the path         set.

updateHookStatus(address,uint8).notice: Updates a hook with a bitmap that indicates its active functionality.         A valid bitmap is any decimal value that is less than or equal         to 7 (0x111).

upgrade(address).notice: Upgrades the contract to a different implementation. This implementation         contract must be compatible with ERC-1822 or else the upgrade will fail.
